»CL1:Wild Compo ?»

This is a quick summary on the budget
so the prices might differ a little,
nothing big though, maybe +- 200-300... 

And if we get a full 700 people,
well, just count like this...
500+(500-100)=700 

Which in the demo contests means
9000+(9000-3000)=15000...

Wow, math can actually be fun
sometimes...

And of course, then there's hard- and
software prices on top of that.


There may also be additional compos
on request, see our homepage for more
info. 

*»CL1: What will it cost?» *

The price is set to »CL1:250 SEK», but that
will probably seem cheap in the end.. 

Girls will as usual enter free of
charge, preferably with a computer of
their own though. 

It is now possible to book a place at
Compusphere too, as usual, check our
homepage for more info. 

*»CL1: When will the party be held? »*

»CL1:Compusphere X» will be held during the
laps of »CL1:October 28» or»CL1: 29» to»CL1: November
1». 

Sadly enough this will create a
conflict between »CL1:Compusphere» and
»CL1:DreamHack», as it is held at the same
time.  This isn't good for anyone of
us really, but we can't move the 
party and neither can they. But I do
not believe that this will be a big
problem though, since there should be
enough enthusiasts in Scandinavia to
fill both parties. And competition,
after all,  will only make both teams
work harder.  

An word of advice: Dont book any
party yet unless you're really sure
about it. And if you should... Book
ours.. =) 

Hmm, by the way, atleast I'm noble
enough to mention their party. =) 

*»CL1: And where then?» *

»CL1:Compusphere» is situated in »CL1:Uddevalla»,
which is a town on the westcoast of
Sweden, about 80 kilometres north of
»CL1:Gothenburg» and 450 kilometres west
of Stockholm. It will be held in
»CL1:Agnebergs-hallen», which is the same
place as last year. Look at the
homepage, it will include a detailed
description on how to get there.
(soon anyway) 

*»CL1: The organizers» *

»CL1:The main organizers», the Galactical
Institute, attends school in
Uddevalla. All members of this crew
are students of Östrabo, a school
teaching natural sciences and
specialising in Computer and 
Information technology. 

The co-organizers, Ward, are an Amiga
based demo group spread out within
100 kilometres from Uddevalla. 

